# useprocess Mobile Workspace Rules

The canonical project location is:

`/Users/amine/Developer/useprocess`

Open and edit the iOS app from:

`/Users/amine/Developer/useprocess/useprocess.xcodeproj`

The Desktop path:

`/Users/amine/Desktop/useprocess`

is only a convenience symlink that points to the canonical Developer folder. Do not treat it as a separate copy.

## What happened

The previous Desktop/iCloud-backed project became unreliable and caused missing-working-directory confusion in Codex/Cursor. The clean source of truth was moved to `/Users/amine/Developer/useprocess`, and the Desktop entry was replaced with a symlink to that folder.

Old broken folders can exist with names like:

`/Users/amine/Desktop/DO_NOT_USE_iCloud_BROKEN_useprocess_*`

Never open, index, edit, restore, or copy from those folders unless the user explicitly asks for forensic recovery.

## Required behavior

- Use `/Users/amine/Developer/useprocess` as the only working directory.
- Do not create duplicate app folders on Desktop, in iCloud Drive, Downloads, or Projects.
- Before editing, confirm `git status --short --branch` from `/Users/amine/Developer/useprocess`.
- Keep generated Xcode data out of the repo: `DerivedData`, `Index.noindex`, `xcuserdata`, `SourcePackages`, `build`.
- Prefer opening the Xcode project with the repo command: `./open-xcode.command`.
- For Firebase/Auth changes, avoid direct `Auth.auth()` access before `FirebaseBootstrap.configure()` and a real `FirebaseApp.app()` check.
- For subscription/paywall work, keep production purchase behavior real. Debug-only test bypasses must stay behind `#if DEBUG`.

## Git

Use the repo on `main` unless the user asks for a branch. After meaningful app changes, build or test when possible, then commit and push only from `/Users/amine/Developer/useprocess`.
